          Hello everybody, is it really necessary to run the etl.py script on a EMR cluster? Can't we just do it on a local spark session or would it take too long?

        • Jose Luis G.

          9:00 AM

          You can run it from your local environment. But take into account that it could take too long. You can get better performance if only retrieves a subset of the whole data specifying a specific path:

          song_data_read_path = os.path.join(input_data, "song_data////.json")
          raw_song_df = spark.read.json(song_data_read_path)
